-- Goldman Sachs profit gets big boost from bond market pickup
-- By Tanya Agrawal and Lauren Tara LaCapra
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 07:40AM EDT
-- None



Oct 16 (Reuters) - Goldman Sachs Group Inc <GS.N> reported a 50 percent rise in  third-quarter net profit on Thursday as last month's sudden pickup in bond market activity boosted trading revenue.

Net income attributable to common shareholders rose to $2.14 billion, or $4.57 per share, in the three months ended Sept. 30  from $1.43 billion, or $2.88 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw6j78pba] Analysts on average had expected earnings of $3.21 per share, according to Thomson Reuters I/B/E/S. It was not immediately clear whether the reported figure was comparable.